eriRouterSysResourcesMib.name: eriRouterSysResourcesMib

revisions.description: Updated RBN/rbn/Rbn as ERICSSON-ROUTER/eriRouter/EriRouter to migrate RBN MIB to ERICSSON MIB.

Add eriRouterChassisAlarmId, eriRouterChassisAlarmType, eriRouterChassisAlarmDateAndTime, eriRouterChassisAlarmDescription, eriRouterChassisAlarmProbableCause, eriRouterChassisAlarmSeverity eriRouterChassisAlarm, eriRouterChassisEventObjectGroup, eriRouterSRMIBCompliance6.
Add new eriRouterSRMIBCompliance, new groups eriRouterSseDiskGroup and eriRouterSseDiskEventObjectGroup, new notification group eriRouterSseDiskNotifyGroup.
Add eriRouterSRMIBCompliance4, new group eriRouterSRPowerExceeded, new notification group eriRouterSRPowerNotifyGroup, and new group eriRouterSRPowerExceededGroup.

Add eriRouterSRStorageSlot, eriRouterSRStorageMountTime, eriRouterSRStorageStatus and eriRouterSRStorageErrors to eriRouterSRStorageTable. Add eriRouterSRStorageFailedEvent to report device failures. Add eriRouterSRMIBCompliance3, eriRouterSRStorageGroup2 and eriRouterSRNotificationGroup2. Add new group eriRouterSRSystem. Add new objects eriRouterSRSystemUptime and eriRouterSRSystemDate.
Add notification eriRouterSRSwitchoverEvent, eriRouterSRMIBCompliance2 and eriRouterSRNotificationGroup.

eriRouterSysResourcesMib.contactinfo: Ericsson AB. Postal: 100 Headquarters Dr San Jose, CA 95134 USA Phone: +1 408 750 5000 Fax: +1 408 750 5599
eriRouterSysResourcesMib.description: The management information definitions for the system resources management of a network device. This MIB is viewable under all contexts.

eriRouterSRProcessNotifyLastUpdate.name: eriRouterSRProcessNotifyLastUpdate
eriRouterSRProcessNotifyLastUpdate.description: The value of sysUpTime when an entry in the eriRouterSRProcessNotifyTable was last added. Because this table is likely to contain many entries, polling of this object allows a management station to determine when re-downloading of the table might be useful.

eriRouterSRProcessEventNotifyEnable.name: eriRouterSRProcessEventNotifyEnable
eriRouterSRProcessEventNotifyEnable.description: Indicates whether eriRouterSRProcessEvent notification should be generated for this system.

eriRouterSRProcessNotifyTable.name: eriRouterSRProcessNotifyTable
eriRouterSRProcessNotifyTable.description: A list of process event notifications since the agent was last re-initialized. If no process event has ever been generated, this table is empty, i.e., has zero entries.

eriRouterSRProcessNotifyEntry.name: eriRouterSRProcessNotifyEntry
eriRouterSRProcessNotifyEntry.description: Information about a death/birth process event notification which was last generated on the particular process.

eriRouterSRProcessNotifyProcName.name: eriRouterSRProcessNotifyProcName
eriRouterSRProcessNotifyProcName.description: A human readable name identifying a particular process in the system.

eriRouterSRProcessNotifyPID.name: eriRouterSRProcessNotifyPID
eriRouterSRProcessNotifyPID.description: A decimal number uniquely identifies the process. The value 0 indicates the process has not been started.

eriRouterSRProcessNotifyEventCause.name: eriRouterSRProcessNotifyEventCause
eriRouterSRProcessNotifyEventCause.description: This identifies the cause of a process death/birth event. The value firstStart(1) indicates the process has been started the first time. The other values identifies the process exit status recorded on the last process death event. On the SmartEdge platform, these values correspond 1-to-1 with the values displayed by the 'show process crash-info' CLI command.

eriRouterSRProcessNotifyEventType.name: eriRouterSRProcessNotifyEventType
eriRouterSRProcessNotifyEventType.description: The type of event notification sent on the process described by this row of the table. The process event type death(1) indicates that the agent has been informed that the process is not available for any use. The event type birth(2) indicates that the agent has been informed that the process has been started.

eriRouterSRProcessNumOfSpawn.name: eriRouterSRProcessNumOfSpawn
eriRouterSRProcessNumOfSpawn.description: The number of times the process has been spawned since the system was last initialized. Note that this is different from the restart of the network management portion of the system.

eriRouterSRProcessNotifyLastTimeSent.name: eriRouterSRProcessNotifyLastTimeSent
eriRouterSRProcessNotifyLastTimeSent.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this notification was last generated on the process.

eriRouterSRStorageTable.name: eriRouterSRStorageTable
eriRouterSRStorageTable.description: The (conceptual) table of long-term storage devices contained by the system. In particular, disk devices accessed remotely over a network are not included here.

eriRouterSRStorageEntry.name: eriRouterSRStorageEntry
eriRouterSRStorageEntry.description: A (conceptual) entry for one long-term storage device contained by the system.

eriRouterSRStorageIndex.name: eriRouterSRStorageIndex
eriRouterSRStorageIndex.description: A unique value for each long-term storage device contained by the system. The value for each physical storage device must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the agent to the next re-initialization.

eriRouterSRStorageDescr.name: eriRouterSRStorageDescr
eriRouterSRStorageDescr.description: A textual description of this storage device, optionally including the device's manufacturer, revision, and its serial number.

eriRouterSRStorageMedia.name: eriRouterSRStorageMedia
eriRouterSRStorageMedia.description: An indication of the type of media used in this long-term storage device.

eriRouterSRStorageRemovable.name: eriRouterSRStorageRemovable
eriRouterSRStorageRemovable.description: Denotes whether or not the storage media may be removed from the drive/slot.

eriRouterSRStorageSize.name: eriRouterSRStorageSize
eriRouterSRStorageSize.description: The total size for this long-term storage device. If the media is removable and is currently removed, this value should be zero.

eriRouterSRStorageUtilization.name: eriRouterSRStorageUtilization
eriRouterSRStorageUtilization.description: This object is the percent utilization of the storage space on a scale of 0 to 100 percent. The formula used to calculate the Utilization is as follows. used blocks * 100 Utilization = --------------------------------------------- free blocks avail to the user + used blocks Note that the divisor is the total number of blocks available to the user which is a subset of the total storage size on the device in eriRouterSRStorageSize.

eriRouterSRStorageSlot.name: eriRouterSRStorageSlot
eriRouterSRStorageSlot.description: The chassis slot number in which the controller card containing this storage device is present.

eriRouterSRStorageMountTime.name: eriRouterSRStorageMountTime
eriRouterSRStorageMountTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this storage device was last mounted.

eriRouterSRStorageStatus.name: eriRouterSRStorageStatus
eriRouterSRStorageStatus.description: The functional status of this storage device.

eriRouterSRStorageErrors.name: eriRouterSRStorageErrors
eriRouterSRStorageErrors.description: The cumulative count of soft errors on this storage device.

eriRouterSseDiskStorageTable.name: eriRouterSseDiskStorageTable
eriRouterSseDiskStorageTable.description: File Server System Blade is a card on the SmartEdge platform that manages data on hard disks connected to the card. This table provides details of these disks.

eriRouterSseDiskStorageEntry.name: eriRouterSseDiskStorageEntry
eriRouterSseDiskStorageEntry.description: A entry for the disk on the SSE.

eriRouterSseDiskSlot.name: eriRouterSseDiskSlot
eriRouterSseDiskSlot.description: The chassis slot number in which the disk resides.

eriRouterSseDiskNum.name: eriRouterSseDiskNum
eriRouterSseDiskNum.description: The disk number used to identity the disk.

eriRouterSseDiskSize.name: eriRouterSseDiskSize
eriRouterSseDiskSize.description: Total size of the disk in GBytes.

eriRouterSseDiskUsed.name: eriRouterSseDiskUsed
eriRouterSseDiskUsed.description: Total disk space utilized in GBytes.

eriRouterSRSystemUptime.name: eriRouterSRSystemUptime
eriRouterSRSystemUptime.description: The amount of time since this system was last initialized. Note that this is different from sysUpTime in the SNMPv2-MIB [RFC1907] because sysUpTime is the uptime of the network management portion of the system.

eriRouterSRSystemDate.name: eriRouterSRSystemDate
eriRouterSRSystemDate.description: The host's notion of the local date and time of day.

eriRouterSRPowerExceededStatus.name: eriRouterSRPowerExceededStatus
eriRouterSRPowerExceededStatus.description: The status of alarm when a controller card is inserted and results in more power being drawn than recommended. If an instance of this object has the value normal, then the chassis power has not exceeded. If an instance of this object has the value failed, then it means the chassis power was exceeded on inserting a controller card.

eriRouterSRProcessEvent.name: eriRouterSRProcessEvent
eriRouterSRProcessEvent.description: This notification is sent each time the agent is informed of a process death/birth event.

eriRouterSRSwitchoverEvent.name: eriRouterSRSwitchoverEvent
eriRouterSRSwitchoverEvent.description: This notification identifies when a switchover occurs from one main processor module to a backup.

eriRouterSRStorageFailedEvent.name: eriRouterSRStorageFailedEvent
eriRouterSRStorageFailedEvent.description: This notification is sent when the value of eriRouterSRStorageStatus for a device changes to 'failed'.

eriRouterSRPowerExceededEvent.name: eriRouterSRPowerExceededEvent
eriRouterSRPowerExceededEvent.description: This notification identifies when a controller card is inserted and results in more power being drawn than recommended.

eriRouterSseDiskAlarmDateAndTime.name: eriRouterSseDiskAlarmDateAndTime
eriRouterSseDiskAlarmDateAndTime.description: The local date and time when the alarm was raised

eriRouterSseDiskAlarmSeverity.name: eriRouterSseDiskAlarmSeverity
eriRouterSseDiskAlarmSeverity.description: The perceived severity of the alarm.

eriRouterSseDiskAlarmProbableCause.name: eriRouterSseDiskAlarmProbableCause
eriRouterSseDiskAlarmProbableCause.description: The probable cause for this alarm.

eriRouterSseDiskAlarmDescription.name: eriRouterSseDiskAlarmDescription
eriRouterSseDiskAlarmDescription.description: A text string which conveys additional information about the alarm.

eriRouterIssuState.name: eriRouterIssuState
eriRouterIssuState.description: The current state of the inservice system upgrade (ISSU).

eriRouterSseDiskHealthDegradedAlarm.name: eriRouterSseDiskHealthDegradedAlarm
eriRouterSseDiskHealthDegradedAlarm.description: A eriRouterSseDiskHealthDegradedAlarm notification signifies that the hard disk health has degraded.

eriRouterSseDiskFailedAlarm.name: eriRouterSseDiskFailedAlarm
eriRouterSseDiskFailedAlarm.description: A eriRouterSseDiskFailedAlarm notification signifies that the hard disk has failed.

eriRouterSseDiskMissingAlarm.name: eriRouterSseDiskMissingAlarm
eriRouterSseDiskMissingAlarm.description: A eriRouterSseDiskMissingAlarm notification signifies that the hard disk is missing.

eriRouterSseDiskUnsupportedAlarm.name: eriRouterSseDiskUnsupportedAlarm
eriRouterSseDiskUnsupportedAlarm.description: A eriRouterSseDiskUnsupportedAlarm notification signifies that the hard disk is not supported.

eriRouterSseDiskOOSAlarm.name: eriRouterSseDiskOOSAlarm
eriRouterSseDiskOOSAlarm.description: A eriRouterSseDiskOOSAlarm notification signifies that the hard disk is out of service.

eriRouterSseDiskVoltageFailureAlarm.name: eriRouterSseDiskVoltageFailureAlarm
eriRouterSseDiskVoltageFailureAlarm.description: A eriRouterSseDiskVoltageFailureAlarm notification signifies that the hard disk voltage has failed.

eriRouterSseDiskOverHeatAlarm.name: eriRouterSseDiskOverHeatAlarm
eriRouterSseDiskOverHeatAlarm.description: A eriRouterSseDiskOverHeatAlarm notification signifies that the hard disk overheating.

eriRouterSseDiskReadFailureAlarm.name: eriRouterSseDiskReadFailureAlarm
eriRouterSseDiskReadFailureAlarm.description: A eriRouterSseDiskReadFailureAlarm notification signifies that the hard disk read failure.

eriRouterIssuStateChange.name: eriRouterIssuStateChange
eriRouterIssuStateChange.description: A notification reporting a change in ISSU state. The new state is returned in the notification.

eriRouterChassisAlarmDateAndTime.name: eriRouterChassisAlarmDateAndTime
eriRouterChassisAlarmDateAndTime.description: The local date and time when the chassis alarm was raised

eriRouterChassisAlarmDescription.name: eriRouterChassisAlarmDescription
eriRouterChassisAlarmDescription.description: A text string which conveys additional information about the chassis alarm.

eriRouterChassisAlarmProbableCause.name: eriRouterChassisAlarmProbableCause
eriRouterChassisAlarmProbableCause.description: The probable cause for the chassis alarm.

eriRouterChassisAlarmSeverity.name: eriRouterChassisAlarmSeverity
eriRouterChassisAlarmSeverity.description: The perceived severity of the chassis alarm.

eriRouterChassisAlarm.name: eriRouterChassisAlarm
eriRouterChassisAlarm.description: A eriRouterChassisAlarm notification signifies that an alarm has been raised/cleared on the chassis.

eriRouterSRMIBCompliance6.name: eriRouterSRMIBCompliance6
eriRouterSRMIBCompliance6.description: The requirements for conformance to the System Resources MIB.

eriRouterSRMIBCompliance.name: eriRouterSRMIBCompliance
eriRouterSRMIBCompliance.description: The requirements for conformance to the System Resources MIB.

eriRouterSRProcessNotifyGroup.name: eriRouterSRProcessNotifyGroup
eriRouterSRProcessNotifyGroup.description: A collection of objects providing for remote monitoring of the system process event notification.

eriRouterSRNotificationGroup2.name: eriRouterSRNotificationGroup2
eriRouterSRNotificationGroup2.description: A collection of notifications that may be implemented for managing the system resources.

eriRouterSRSystemGroup.name: eriRouterSRSystemGroup
eriRouterSRSystemGroup.description: A collection of objects providing for remote monitoring of the system information.

eriRouterSRPowerNotifyGroup.name: eriRouterSRPowerNotifyGroup
eriRouterSRPowerNotifyGroup.description: A notification that may be implemented for tracking power capacity exceeding limit.

eriRouterSRPowerExceededGroup.name: eriRouterSRPowerExceededGroup
eriRouterSRPowerExceededGroup.description: A group providing for status of the power capacity exceeding limit.

eriRouterSseDiskGroup.name: eriRouterSseDiskGroup
eriRouterSseDiskGroup.description: A group providing SSE disk details.

eriRouterSseDiskEventObjectGroup.name: eriRouterSseDiskEventObjectGroup
eriRouterSseDiskEventObjectGroup.description: A collection of eriRouterSseDisk notification objects.

eriRouterSseDiskNotifyGroup.name: eriRouterSseDiskNotifyGroup

eriRouterIssuGroup.name: eriRouterIssuGroup
eriRouterIssuGroup.description: A collection of ISSU notification objects.

eriRouterIssuNotifyGroup.name: eriRouterIssuNotifyGroup

eriRouterChassisEventObjectGroup.name: eriRouterChassisEventObjectGroup

eriRouterChassisNotifyGroup.name: eriRouterChassisNotifyGroup
eriRouterChassisNotifyGroup.description: Notifications that are implemented for chassis.

eriRouterSRMIBCompliance3.description: The requirements for conformance to the System Resources MIB.

eriRouterSRMIBCompliance4.description: The requirements for conformance to the System Resources MIB.

eriRouterSRStorageGroup.description: The System Resources Storage Group. Replaced by eriRouterSRStorageGroup2.
